title: Vegetable Soup
directions: Season beef with salt and pepper; heat a large soup pot over med high heat and add
about - 1 Tbsp. oil to the pot and brown meat.
When the meat is browned add onions, celery, carrots and garlic; let cook until
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, beef broth, chicken broth and water.
Cover and let cook over med heat for about 40 min. or until beef is tender.
When the beef is tender; uncover; add mushrooms, cabbage, green beans and herbs.
Cook for an additional 15 – 20 min. over med heat or until cabbage and green beans
ingredients: 2 pounds beef chuck, cut into small cubes
1 ½ tsp. kosher salt (plus more for meat)
¼ tsp. black pepper (plus more for meat)
½ head cabbage, cut into bite sized pieces
8 oz. frozen or fresh green beans (1/2 pound)
